      • saveArtifact

        public void saveArtifact(com.offbytwo.jenkins.JenkinsServer jenkins,
                         String jobName,
                         int buildNumber,
                         String artifactName,
                         File outputFile)
                  throws DiggerClientException,
                         IOException
        Save artifact for specified location for specific job, build number and artifact name. If name would be an regular expression method would return stream for the first match.
        Parameters:
        jobName - name of the job
        buildNumber - job build number
        artifactName - name of the artifact to fetch - can be regexp for example *.apk
        outputFile - file (location) used to save artifact
        Throws:
        DiggerClientException - when problem with fetching artifacts from jenkins
        IOException - when one of the files cannot be saved

      • streamArtifact

        public InputStream streamArtifact(com.offbytwo.jenkins.JenkinsServer jenkins,
                                  String jobName,
                                  int buildNumber,
                                  String artifactName)
                           throws DiggerClientException
        Get artifact inputstream for specific job, build number and artifact name. If name would be an regular expression method would return stream for the first match.
        Parameters:
        jobName - name of the job
        buildNumber - job build number
        artifactName - name of the artifact to fetch - can be regexp for example *.apk
        Returns:
        InputStream with file contents that can be saved or piped to socket
        Throws:
        DiggerClientException - when problem with fetching artifacts from jenkins
